00:12:44,650 --> 00:12:45,060
Bye.

277
00:13:17,820 --> 00:13:18,210
Mi Qiao.

278
00:13:21,090 --> 00:13:21,860
You are late.

279
00:13:22,180 --> 00:13:23,450
Zhouzhou already left with Lin Yang.

280
00:13:24,820 --> 00:13:25,890
Did she get wet in the rain?

281
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:27,130
No. She brought an umbrella.

282
00:13:27,690 --> 00:13:28,380
Why didn't you?

283
00:13:28,690 --> 00:13:29,940
No need for such a light rain.

284
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,060
Sometimes I feel that you are not really like a girl.

285
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,740
Truly I am not. So what?

286
00:13:35,010 --> 00:13:35,500
Don't move.

287
00:13:43,820 --> 00:13:44,210
What are you doing?

288
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:47,690
What's the matter again?

289
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:49,330
What happened? You don't feel comfortable again?

290
00:13:50,450 --> 00:13:51,060
No.

291
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:53,260
Um, Zhouzhou has left already

292
00:13:53,260 --> 00:13:54,330
and you don't have to follow me anymore.

293
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:57,380
What's wrong with you lately?

294
00:13:57,420 --> 00:13:58,500
Sometimes you were going well and sometimes you weren't.

295
00:13:59,330 --> 00:14:00,010
I don't know.

296
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:02,620
Let's go to my place and take some BBQ.

297
00:14:02,690 --> 00:14:03,500
I don't feel like it.

298
00:14:04,130 --> 00:14:05,500
Or I teach you to play pool.

299
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:06,530
I'm not interested.

300
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:07,770
Fine, tell me what you want to do

301
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:09,180
and I will follow you anyway today.

302
00:14:12,820 --> 00:14:13,930
How about

303
00:14:14,450 --> 00:14:15,690
making an expedition?

304
00:14:16,090 --> 00:14:16,770
Where?

305
00:14:16,980 --> 00:14:18,260
I won't do anything illegal.

306
00:14:19,130 --> 00:14:20,530
When I was a child, my dad told me

307
00:14:20,740 --> 00:14:22,820
that there are treasures hidden at the end of rainbow.

308
00:14:24,010 --> 00:14:25,330
It's just a trick that you dad played on a child like you.

309
00:14:25,860 --> 00:14:26,330
Tell me.

310
00:14:26,740 --> 00:14:28,210
Can a rainbow get down to the earth?

311
00:14:28,530 --> 00:14:29,420
How can it have an end?

312
00:14:29,680 --> 00:14:31,620
It's true. I've seen it with my own eyes.

313
00:14:32,530 --> 00:14:33,450
So did you dig up the treasure?

314
00:14:34,380 --> 00:14:35,730
I was just coming back to my senses

315
00:14:35,770 --> 00:14:37,210
when the rainbow disappeared.

316
00:14:38,500 --> 00:14:39,690
You really think I'm stupid?

317
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:42,940
If you do not believe, I'll go back to find photos to show you.

318
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,260
Okay, then do not take fake photos to fool me.

319
00:14:46,570 --> 00:14:48,210
Once I give Huang Mao the photo, I'll know the truth.

320
00:14:48,610 --> 00:14:49,860
You just don't believe me, do you?

321
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:52,300
No, this kind of science-based thing

322
00:14:52,420 --> 00:14:53,380
can not be debated.

323
00:14:54,090 --> 00:14:55,300
No education, no common sense.

324
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:57,330
I tell you, when the time comes, don't beg me to take you to dig for gold.

325
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:58,260
I won't share the gold with you even if I dig it up.

326
00:14:58,740 --> 00:14:59,770
Who do you think is uneducated?

327
00:14:59,980 --> 00:15:00,980
You are the uneducated one.

328
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:03,770
I'm talking about you, get lost!

329
00:15:07,330 --> 00:15:08,860
A person who failed geology

330
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:10,180
is not qualified to brag.

331
00:15:11,530 --> 00:15:12,610
Take out your exam paper, please.

332
00:15:13,210 --> 00:15:14,260
The difficulty of the paper this time

333
00:15:14,530 --> 00:15:16,090
still has some way to go before the college entrance examination.

334
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:17,740
Evaluate yourself

335
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:18,860
about your current level.

336
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:20,540
[Zhenhua High School, Second semester of sophomore year, Math Test (Liberal Arts) , 109]

337
00:15:21,260 --> 00:15:22,130
What's worthy of praise is that

338
00:15:22,690 --> 00:15:24,890
Ling Xiangqian and Yu Zhouzhou

339
00:15:25,330 --> 00:15:26,860
have the highest score in our class.

340
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,130
They all got 145 points.

341
00:15:28,820 --> 00:15:29,690
After class,

342
00:15:29,770 --> 00:15:31,000
go and check their papers.

343
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:32,320
Learn more about their problem-solving ideas.

344
00:15:33,620 --> 00:15:34,450
Some students

345
00:15:35,260 --> 00:15:37,050
may have some great progress in other subjects.

346
00:15:37,650 --> 00:15:38,740
But they will lose many points

347
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:39,740
in math.

348
00:15:40,450 --> 00:15:41,690
This will be very disadvantageous in the college entrance examination.

349
00:15:42,570 --> 00:15:44,530
Mathematics is not a subject for quick success.

350
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:46,500
We have to be more practical.

351
00:15:47,290 --> 00:15:49,820
Improve yourselves day by day with diligence.

352
00:15:51,210 --> 00:15:53,300
OK, that will be all for today.

353
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:54,820
For the rest of your class, study by yourselves.

354
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:57,450
That's OK if Benben doesn't believe me.

355
00:15:57,450 --> 00:15:58,620
But that's not OK if you don't believe me.

356
00:15:58,820 --> 00:16:00,770
That's impossible!

357
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:02,890
I'm telling you, Yu Zhouzhou, what will happen if I find it?

358
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,260
Nothing will happen.

359
00:16:04,820 --> 00:16:06,500
If I find it, you will buy me kebabs.

360
00:16:06,820 --> 00:16:08,690
OK, that's on me. Deal.

361
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:09,420
Wait for it.

362
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:09,970
Waiting.

363
00:16:13,210 --> 00:16:14,180
That's impossible.

364
00:16:15,650 --> 00:16:16,740
That's impossible.

365
00:16:17,860 --> 00:16:19,010
Still denying it.

366
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:27,860
Come to my office during lunch break.

367
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:31,860
I've just found it.

368
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:35,690
I should have torn out that page.

369
00:16:35,690 --> 00:16:36,300
I believe in you.

370
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:37,380
I believe in you.

371
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:41,690
Zhouzhou, just come with me.

372
00:16:43,180 --> 00:16:44,860
Stealing books from Director Pan's office?

373
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,450
You are being more and more outrageous.

374
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:48,060
I'll tear out the most important page.

375
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:49,180
Director Pan will never find out.

376
00:16:49,210 --> 00:16:49,690
I promise.

377
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:51,180
You can always buy another book.

378
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,380
I can't.

379
00:16:52,450 --> 00:16:53,620
That book was published several years ago.

380
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:54,530
I have been looking for it for a long time.

381
00:16:56,180 --> 00:16:58,130
When did you become so interested in geography?

382
00:16:58,940 --> 00:17:00,060
I'm not interested.

383
00:17:00,380 --> 00:17:01,300
I just want to fight about it.

384
00:17:02,450 --> 00:17:03,420
Another bet with Ben Ben?

385
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:04,680
How do you know?

386
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:05,890
By the way, Zhouzhou.

387
00:17:06,290 --> 00:17:08,290
You are on my side, right?

388
00:17:14,260 --> 00:17:14,569
Xin Rui

389
00:17:15,020 --> 00:17:16,020
Are you heading to the teacher's office?

390
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:17,540
Give the paper to Mr. Zhang for me by the way.

391
00:17:17,619 --> 00:17:18,020
Thanks.

392
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:21,170
You didn't write your name.

393
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,140
You can write it for me.

394
00:17:31,210 --> 00:17:34,870
[Lin Yang]

395
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,690
Zhouzhou, watch out for me.

396
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:39,800
I'll be back in three minutes.

397
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:40,170
OK.

398
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:41,290
If I get caught,

399
00:17:41,780 --> 00:17:42,770
just abandon me and leave.

400
00:17:42,930 --> 00:17:44,620
You've got more important tasks to accomplish.

401
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:45,620
Be quick!

402
00:17:45,620 --> 00:17:46,620
In case Director Pan comes!

403
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:47,780
Go for it!

404
00:17:47,860 --> 00:17:48,170
Go for it!

405
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,530
Guess who I am.

406
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,210
Lin Yang, stop it!

407
00:17:58,450 --> 00:17:59,380
I'm doing business here.

408
00:17:59,400 --> 00:17:59,930
What business?

409
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:01,090
Look out for Mi Qiao.

410
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:02,620
What is Mi Qiao doing in there?

411
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:03,290
Stealing books.

412
00:18:04,810 --> 00:18:05,260
What book?

413
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:07,050
Mr. Zhang.

414
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:07,690
Mr. Zhang.

415
00:18:08,260 --> 00:18:09,740
What are you two doing sneaking around here?

416
00:18:11,090 --> 00:18:13,210
I am accompanying Yu Zhouzhou to ask questions.

417
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:15,620
She's a liberal art student.

418
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,410
Do you come here with her to ask chemistry questions?

419
00:18:18,050 --> 00:18:18,410
Nope.

420
00:18:19,690 --> 00:18:20,050
Lin Yang,

421
00:18:20,050 --> 00:18:21,660
you are not understanding the situation, right?

422
00:18:23,050 --> 00:18:24,540
You two still have the courage to do this.

423
00:18:25,690 --> 00:18:26,290
What is it?

424
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:28,980
OK, go back to your class.

425
00:18:29,890 --> 00:18:31,860
Mr. Zhang, you can't go in now.

426
00:18:32,090 --> 00:18:32,450
What's wrong?

427
00:18:32,930 --> 00:18:33,290
Because

428
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:34,450
Mr. Wu is in there.

429
00:18:34,690 --> 00:18:35,020
Yes.

430
00:18:36,540 --> 00:18:37,490
Exactly, I need to talk to him.

431
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,210
Mr. Wu and Director Pan

432
00:18:40,210 --> 00:18:41,140
are talking about something very important.

433
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:45,290
Then I'll wait here for them for a while.

434
00:18:51,330 --> 00:18:51,800
Mr. Zhang,

435
00:18:52,260 --> 00:18:53,810
about the math question that you talked about last time,

436
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:55,020
I think the steps are too complicated.

437
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:55,810
I have a quick solution.

438
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:56,500
Let's see the results.

439
00:18:57,620 --> 00:18:58,090
What's wrong with you?

440
00:18:58,210 --> 00:18:59,810
I don't really like to discuss about math questions with top students.

441
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:01,900
By the way, Yu Zhouzhou.

442
00:19:02,410 --> 00:19:02,980
Come with me.

443
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:04,210
Take back the homework of your class!

444
00:19:25,570 --> 00:19:27,620
I will also ask Mr. Zhang about Lin Yang's situation.

445
00:19:28,020 --> 00:19:30,540
It seems that they were classmates since childhood.

446
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:32,380
So they are closer than other students.

447
00:19:32,450 --> 00:19:33,900
You don't always have to be so nervous.

448
00:19:34,660 --> 00:19:36,490
It clearly writes two students' names

449
00:19:36,490 --> 00:19:37,410
in this report letter.

450
00:19:38,330 --> 00:19:40,170
This seriously affects the learning culture of the school.

451
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,930
I don't think it's a fabrication.

452
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:43,620
I think,

453
00:19:44,200 --> 00:19:45,450
the problem is not about those two kids.

454
00:19:45,740 --> 00:19:46,570
But about the report letter.

455
00:19:47,090 --> 00:19:48,620
I've always been teaching these students

456
00:19:48,980 --> 00:19:50,330
to be honest and open.

457
00:19:50,540 --> 00:19:51,690
If students have complaints,

458
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:53,170
why not bring those up on the table?

459
00:19:53,260 --> 00:19:54,260
They can also talk to the teachers.

460
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:56,810
Why do they have to write an anonymous report letter?

461
00:19:56,810 --> 00:19:58,020
How boring is that?

462
00:19:58,290 --> 00:19:59,540
I have to look at the bigger picture.

463
00:20:00,260 --> 00:20:02,210
I can't let a fish foul a pot of soup.

464
00:20:03,090 --> 00:20:04,380
You have to cooperate with me on this.

465
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:05,560
No, I can't.

466
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:07,090
This is not the bigger picture.

467
00:20:07,260 --> 00:20:08,530
I have to take care of my students.

468
00:20:09,020 --> 00:20:09,930
I can't let them

469
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,610
be treated unjustly.

470
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,330
I have to talk with him.

471
00:20:17,660 --> 00:20:18,740
At least make a promise to me.

472
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:19,930
Can't take it too far.

473
00:20:21,260 --> 00:20:22,330
These two are top students.

474
00:20:22,330 --> 00:20:23,380
You have to take care of them.

475
00:20:23,780 --> 00:20:25,540
Can't let them choose the wrong way.

476
00:20:26,020 --> 00:20:27,780
Wrong, how wrong will it be?

477
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:32,260
There aren't many wrong ways, idiot.

478
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:35,810
What's the matter with you?

479
00:20:35,980 --> 00:20:36,330
Nothing.

480
00:20:37,540 --> 00:20:38,620
The water is too hot.

481
00:20:40,290 --> 00:20:40,740
Well,

482
00:20:41,330 --> 00:20:42,570
I'm telling you, believing me is a safe bet.

483
00:20:43,740 --> 00:20:44,330
Can't be wrong.

484
00:20:45,260 --> 00:20:46,980
Something is wrong.

485
00:20:47,740 --> 00:20:48,930
I have to find Mr. Zhang to talk about it.

486
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:50,050
Go ahead then.

487
00:20:54,930 --> 00:20:55,620
Come out.

488
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:57,290
What are you doing?

489
00:20:57,780 --> 00:20:59,140
I'm sorry, Mr. Wu.

490
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:00,490
Sorry for what?

491
00:21:00,540 --> 00:21:02,210
What are you doing here?

492
00:21:02,450 --> 00:21:04,410
Director Pan confiscated my magazine.

493
00:21:04,540 --> 00:21:06,980
I want to tear one page out.

494
00:21:07,650 --> 00:21:09,570
How dare you!

495
00:21:10,400 --> 00:21:12,090
I'm scared to death, go to class now!

496
00:21:12,900 --> 00:21:15,170
I'm sorry, Mr. Wu. Thank you.

497
00:21:23,210 --> 00:21:24,380
Class dismissed!

498
00:21:24,540 --> 00:21:25,040
Stand up.

499
00:21:26,380 --> 00:21:29,330
Goodbye, teacher.

500
00:21:31,810 --> 00:21:32,260
Master,

501
00:21:32,970 --> 00:21:35,020
I'm looking out for you.

502
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:38,140
Who knows that I was called by Mr. Zhang to get the homework.

503
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:40,930
Master,

504
00:21:41,290 --> 00:21:42,980
I think a ninja like you

505
00:21:43,380 --> 00:21:44,450
will surely get out.

506
00:21:45,050 --> 00:21:47,690
I didn't expect to meet Director Pan and Mr. Wu.

507
00:21:47,930 --> 00:21:49,370
I deserve a thousand death penalties.

508
00:21:51,050 --> 00:21:52,860
I'm doing this for you.

509
00:21:54,140 --> 00:21:55,860
If I hadn't gone to read that report letter,

510
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:57,290
how would I have been blocked in the room.

511
00:21:58,330 --> 00:22:00,210
The report letter has nothing to do with me.

512
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:02,500
I've seen the letter.

513
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:04,170
Someone report the relationship between you and Lin Yang.

514
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:05,380
Get prepared.

515
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:07,290
Zhou Zhou, Mi Qiao

516
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:12,660
Lin Yang got caught.

517
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,210
He was called to the office by Director Pan.

518
00:22:14,780 --> 00:22:15,260
It's over.

519
00:22:15,330 --> 00:22:17,330
It must be about the report letter.

520
00:22:17,330 --> 00:22:18,320
I'll go to Director Pan to straighten things out.

521
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,570
Stop, on this point,

522
00:22:19,570 --> 00:22:20,810
don't get in the way.

523
00:22:20,900 --> 00:22:21,290
That's right.

524
00:22:21,290 --> 00:22:22,570
Lin Yang asked me to pass on three words to you:

525
00:22:22,810 --> 00:22:24,160
honesty and dependability.

526
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:25,090
He said that

527
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:26,290
things will be straightened out by me.

528
00:22:26,660 --> 00:22:27,930
That's my man.

529
00:22:28,010 --> 00:22:29,090
Reckless!

530
00:22:29,540 --> 00:22:31,410
Don't hand yourself over, good lord!

531
00:22:31,500 --> 00:22:33,020
That's right, wait for him to come back to get the story straight.

532
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:33,900
It's never too late to go in then.

533
00:22:34,290 --> 00:22:36,410
What a mess!

534
00:22:39,380 --> 00:22:39,740
Lin Yang,

535
00:22:40,380 --> 00:22:41,740
one question, one answer.

536
00:22:42,410 --> 00:22:44,570
When did you and Yu Zhouzhou meet?

537
00:22:44,970 --> 00:22:46,020
We've known each other since we were kids.

538
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:47,280
Not only did I know her,

539
00:22:47,690 --> 00:22:48,860
but also my parents.

540
00:22:49,170 --> 00:22:49,620
She's more than an acquaintance.

541
00:22:50,020 --> 00:22:51,330
She used to play at my house when I was a kid.

542
00:22:51,570 --> 00:22:52,330
And at that time...

543
00:22:52,330 --> 00:22:53,930
One question, one answer.

544
00:22:54,260 --> 00:22:55,290
Don't answer questions that I never ask.

545
00:22:57,810 --> 00:23:00,260
Have you ever

546
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:02,660
crossed over the boundaries of being classmates?

547
00:23:03,780 --> 00:23:05,410
Like physical contacts.

548
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:09,780
Yes.

549
00:23:10,140 --> 00:23:10,620
You see.

550
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:11,810
We have held hands.

551
00:23:12,330 --> 00:23:12,930
When?

552
00:23:13,210 --> 00:23:13,810
First semester of senior year.

553
00:23:15,570 --> 00:23:17,020
Who gave you so much courage?

554
00:23:17,140 --> 00:23:17,740
You.

555
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:20,290
